1 a. 9 p.  _ Thousands of troops arrive at the west side of the square and some of the riflemen open fire. m.  _ Troops straggle away from their positions near the square, walking in small groups followed by watchful residents.  _ Troops hurl tear gas then open fire on the crowds. 5 a.  Saturday (12 noon EDT Friday) _ Tens of thousands of troops enter Beijing from the east marching toward Tiananmen Square, China's symbolic political heart.  Sunday.  _ Demonstrators, many walking hand-in-hand, begin leaving the square, ending their three-week occupation. More people shot as troops fire at crowds. 2 a. 